<li>Write single e-mail address on each line. &nbsp;This can include the
person's name <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>i.e.</i>  Dave Smith &#60;dsmith@anispsomewhere.net&#62;
<BR>

<li>When you have the list completed, Press Ctrl+W to save mailing list to
file -- replace default file name QUICKPAD.TXT with desired list name,
<i>eg.</i> "everyone"  or "family" or "students"  (<i>NO</i> extension on the
file name; simply STUDENTS -- <I>not</i> STUDENTS.TXT)<br>

<li>To send e-mail to a list, type @listname in the <i>To:</i> field.
&nbsp;Single-recipient lists can be used as nicknames.<br>

<li><I><b>Tip:</b></i>&nbsp; Because of problems with SPAM e-mail, many ISPs have
their servers set to limit the maximum number of names a message will be
sent to; the server counts the actual recipients, and will stop sending
when the limit is reached. You probably will not know if this happens, so
before creating long lists, check with your internet provider to find out
any limits.<br>

<li>You can also add <A HREF="mailto:@everyone">mailto:@everyone</A> style
URLs to your Hotlist.
<BR>
